[src:ordinary-differential-equations/sturm-liouville-theory] This particular Fourier series is troublesome because of its poor convergence properties.
[src:ordinary-differential-equations/sturm-liouville-theory] It is not clear *a priori* whether the series converges pointwise.
[src:ordinary-differential-equations/sturm-liouville-theory] Because of Fourier analysis, since the Fourier coefficients are "square-summable", the Fourier series converges in *L*2 which is all we need for this particular theory to function.
